# Packages installed by modules/60-dev-tools.sh.
# One apt package name per line. Lines starting with # (and blank lines) are
# ignored. This is the "add stuff here as you go" extension point for dev
# tooling — add a package name, commit, and re-run install.sh to pick it up.
# Nothing here is pentest-specific; keep it that way.
#
# Deliberately NOT listed here, because they're already guaranteed elsewhere
# (apt_install() would just no-op on them, but keep this list free of dead
# weight):
#   - git, curl, tmux: pulled in directly by Kali's own kali-system-core /
#     kali-linux-headless metapackages on any standard install
#   - build-essential, jq: installed automatically by 00-pimpmykali.sh's
#     `--autonoroot` run (pimpmykali's fix_missing/fix_ghidra steps)

unzip
